long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1209550 log-file from Eclipse
Description of problem:
GUI doesn't start.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):
1:4.6.1-2.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible:
100%
Steps to Reproduce:
1. Start GUI from Menu 2. Splash appears 3. Eclipse doesn't start
Actual results:
Eclipse doesn't start. Gives errors in log-file.
Expected results:
Eclipse starts without problems.
Additional info:
see attached log-file.
Eclipse was installed using: dnf group install 'Fedora Eclipse'
This might be related to the retirement of glassfish-el-api on f25 and rawhide (see fedora-java list)

Downgraded glassfish-el to glassfish-el-3.0.0-6.fc24.noarch and Eclipse started working again.
Thank you very much!
Unresolved requirement: Import-Package: javax.el; version="[3.0.0,4.0.0)" javax.el now comes from glassfish-el-api sub package
even having `glassfish-el-api`-package installed doesn't fix it; gets pulled as an implicit Requires anyways, but doesn't solve the issue… :(
Reopening and re-assigning to glassfish-el package…

The attached log-file is the error generated, when starting Eclipse and having `glassfish-el-3.0.1-0.1.b08.fc25`, `glassfish-el-api-3.0.1-0.1.b08.fc25` installed. Downgrading to `glassfish-el-3.0.0-6.fc24.noarch` instantly solves that and Eclipse starts working again.

I don't think this is a bug on the glassfish-el side, since it's Eclipse that actually requires (and symlinks) the bundle (http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/fileinfo?rpmID=8133940&filename=/usr/lib64/eclipse/plugins/com.sun.el.javax.el_3.0.0.jar) . I think a rebuild with the correct Requires should probably fix this.

(In reply to Björn "besser82" Esser from comment #8) > The attached log-file is the error generated, when starting Eclipse and > having `glassfish-el-3.0.1-0.1.b08.fc25`, > `glassfish-el-api-3.0.1-0.1.b08.fc25` installed. Downgrading to > `glassfish-el-3.0.0-6.fc24.noarch` instantly solves that and Eclipse starts > working again.
Pushed a new glassfish-el-3.0.1-0.1.b08 build
Rawhide Task info: http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=16063308 F25 Task info: http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=16063725 have time for try also this one?

Created attachment 1209751 log-files with glassfish-el-api-3.0.1-0.2.b08.fc25.noarch
Tried with `glassfish-el-api-3.0.1-0.2.b08.fc25.noarch`… Eclipse still fails to start… :(
